               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 1ra-53va),
                     incomplete
 - Homily by ʾabbā Salāmā, Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols.
                     9ra-12rb)
 - Homily by St Jacob of Serug for the funeral of priests and
                     deacons (fols. 12rb-17va) 
 - Discourse of St Athanasius on death (fols.
                     28ra-37va) 
 - Maṣḥaf za-wäḍʾat ʾǝm-ʾIyarusalem “Book that Came from
                     Jerusalem” (fols. 41rb-53va)
 II) Maṣḥafa qedar “Book of the Jar” (fols.
                     53va-61rb)
 III) Maṣḥafa krǝstǝnnā “Book of the Christening” (fols.
                     61va-84vb), incomplete</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Text III is called Maṣḥafa krǝstǝnnā in the incipit (<locus target="#61va">61va</locus>).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
